Subject: [PATCH] Phase 1: Graphical pitch envelope editor with drag handles
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the four scalar pitch knobs (start, end, decay, curve) with an
interactive curve canvas. Three draggable handles directly manipulate the
underlying params:
- Left handle: pitch_start (vertical, log freq axis)
- Right handle: pitch_end + decay (vertical freq, horizontal log time)
- Middle handle: curve exponent (vertical drag reshapes the sweep)

Frequency axis is log 20–800 Hz with gridlines at 50/100/200/400. Time
axis is log 0.05–2.0 s. The curve handle inverts the freq formula to
solve for the new exponent. Double-click any handle to reset its param
to default. Numeric readout under the plot shows live values.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
